From Sun Star, Davao, January 4, 2010:
--------------------------------------

Maguindanao massacre DVD sold in Davao.

LIKE a constant reminder of the brutality of the Ampatuan massacre, DVD copies of video clips entitled &quot;Maguindanao Massacre 11/23/09ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚ï¿½ is now available even in the city. A look-see at DVD stalls here revealed the item has been available just around two weeks after the November 23, 2009 massacre. From what he has seen of the video, the vendor said, the clips could have been taken by one of the Scene of the Crime Operatives of the Philippine National Police (PNP).

The film, which runs for more than four hours, covers the first two days of the retrieval operation by authorities in Barangay Salman in Ampatuan town where 57 civilians were abducted and murdered, easily called the worst election-related crime in Philippine history. The DVD features a hand-held video of authorities exhuming the bodies of the victims: disfigured, blood-soaked or blood-drained from the force of gunshots or from being run over by the backhoe.
